# Math 


$$T = \frac{1}{A + B\ln(R) + C \ln(R)^3}$$

$$V_{\text{out} }= V_\text{in} \frac{R}{R + R_{1}}$$

(Vo/Vi) = R/(R+R1)
(Vo/Vi)(R+R1) = R
(Vo/Vi)R+(Vo/Vi)R1 = R
(Vo/Vi)*R1 = R - (Vo/Vi)R
(Vo/Vi)*R1 = R (1- (Vo/Vi))
(Vo/Vi)*R1 * 1/(1- (Vo/Vi)) = R

Measure voltage at 3 different temps.
Do a linear fit to get the 3 consts.

Solve with matrix

The calculated cooeffitions are
A = 2.396442e-03
B = -3.240759e-04 
C = 8.87993e-07
